Function Reference/sanitize comment cookies « WordPress Codex
-----------

Sanitizes the cookies sent to the user already.

Will only do anything if the cookies have already been created for the
user. Mostly used after cookies had been sent to use elsewhere.

Usage
-----

` <?php sanitize_comment_cookies() ?> `

Parameters
----------

None

Return Values
-------------

 (void) 
:   This function does not return a value.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    with 'pre\_comment\_author\_name' on 'comment\_author' cookie
-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    with 'pre\_comment\_author\_email' on 'comment\_author\_email'
    cookie
-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    with 'pre\_comment\_author\_url' on 'comment\_author\_url' cookie

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.0.4

Source File
-----------

`sanitize_comment_cookies()` is located in `wp-includes/comment.php`.

